			<h1 class="entry-title">Interview With Crypto ‘Optimist’ Brian Kelly: Bitcoin Is Still 50 Percent Undervalued</h1>		</header><!-- .entry-header -->
		<div class="conteudo-post">
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="entry-date"> <i class="icon-circle glyphicon glyphicon-calendar"></i> <time class="entry-date" datetime="2019-02-16T21:52:00+00:00">16 de fevereiro de 2019</time></span> <i class="icon-circle glyphicon glyphicon-user"></i> <span class="author vcard">Por <a class="url fn n" href="https://www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/author/mastercontrole/" rel="author">Eduardo Menezes</a></span> <i class="icon-circle glyphicon glyphicon-comment"></i>0 comentários <i class="icon-circle glyphicon glyphicon-folder-open"></i><a href="https://www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/category/bitcoin/" rel="category tag">Bitcoin</a>, <a href="https://www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/category/bitcoin-news/" rel="category tag">Bitcoin News</a>				<hr>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
										<div class="entry-content">
					<div><img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/528_aHR0cHM6Ly9zMy5jb2ludGVsZWdyYXBoLmNvbS9zdG9yYWdlL3VwbG9hZHMvdmlldy84MDZiYzFmOGUzYjdiOWYzZGUzMDBmZTg5Mzk0MGM4MS5qcGc3D.jpg?w=600&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/528_aHR0cHM6Ly9zMy5jb2ludGVsZWdyYXBoLmNvbS9zdG9yYWdlL3VwbG9hZHMvdmlldy84MDZiYzFmOGUzYjdiOWYzZGUzMDBmZTg5Mzk0MGM4MS5qcGc3D.jpg?w=600&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" class=" jetpack-lazy-image"><noscript><img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.eduardomenezes.com/crypto/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/528_aHR0cHM6Ly9zMy5jb2ludGVsZWdyYXBoLmNvbS9zdG9yYWdlL3VwbG9hZHMvdmlldy84MDZiYzFmOGUzYjdiOWYzZGUzMDBmZTg5Mzk0MGM4MS5qcGc3D.jpg?w=600&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1"></noscript>From what it was like to work for Lehman Brothers to the sentiment analysis of the crypto market and the signs of the next financial crisis — we talked to CNBC’s analyst Brian Kelly about everything</p>
